ach O'Cathain of the Isles, Limavady27歲。他於1410年之前與Alice FitzGerald在愛爾蘭庫迪 泰龍結婚。他們至少是1個女兒的父母。他去世於大約1444年在英國蘇格蘭音巴內-爾登維根享年76歲，埋葬在蘇格蘭。"},"zh-hans":{"about 1370–abt 1444":"大约1370年–大约1444年","1350–1426":"1350年–1426年","1370–1444":"1370年–1444年","1380–Female":"1380年–殁","1410–1485":"1410年–1485年","1340–1395":"1340年–1395年","1345–1368":"1345年–1368年","about 1370":"大约1370年","before 1410":"1410年之前","1395":"1395年","1340":"1340年","1350":"1350年","1370":"1370年","1380":"1380年","abt 1444":"大约1444年","1426":"1426年","1368":"1368年","1345":"1345年","1444":"1444年","1410":"1410年","1485":"1485年","about 1444":"大约1444年","about 1365":"大约1365年","County Tyrone, Irland":"爱尔兰庫迪 泰龍","Ireland":"爱尔兰","Dunnyveg Castle, Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"英国苏格兰音巴內-爾登維根","Scotland":"苏格兰","County Tyrone, Ireland":"爱尔兰庫迪 泰龍","lifeSummary":"当Conn Baccach O'Neill于大约1370年出生在爱尔兰庫迪 泰龍时，他的父亲Muircheartach Ceannfhada MacÉnri, Lord of Clandeboye Ó'Néill31岁，母亲Agnes Aine Cumach O'Cathain of the Isles, Limavady27岁。他于1410年之前与Alice FitzGerald在爱尔兰庫迪 泰龍结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。他去世于大约1444年在英国苏格兰音巴內-爾登維根享年76岁，埋葬在苏格兰。"},"hr":{"about 1370–abt 1444":"oko 1370.–oko 1444.","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1380–Female":"1380–preminula","1410–1485":"1410.–1485","1340–1395":"1340–1395.","1345–1368":"1345–1368","about 1370":"oko 1370.","before 1410":"prije 1410.","1395":"1395.","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","abt 1444":"oko 1444.","1426":"1426","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1444":"1444","1410":"1410.","1485":"1485","about 1444":"oko 1444.","about 1365":"oko 1365.","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Irska","Ireland":"Irska","Dunnyveg Castle, Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Škotska, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","County Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Irska"},"cs":{"about 1370–abt 1444":"okolo 1370–okolo 1444","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1380–Female":"1380–Zesnulá","1410–1485":"1410–1485","1340–1395":"1340–1395","1345–1368":"1345–1368","about 1370":"okolo 1370","before 1410":"před 1410","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","abt 1444":"okolo 1444","1426":"1426","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1485":"1485","about 1444":"okolo 1444","about 1365":"okolo 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Irsko","Ireland":"Irsko","Dunnyveg Castle, Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Skotsko, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","County Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Irsko"},"da":{"about 1370–abt 1444":"omkring 1370–omkring 1444","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1380–Female":"1380–Afdød","1410–1485":"1410–1485","1340–1395":"1340–1395","1345–1368":"1345–1368","about 1370":"omkring 1370","before 1410":"før 1410","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","abt 1444":"omkring 1444","1426":"1426","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1485":"1485","about 1444":"omkring 1444","about 1365":"omkring 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Irland","Ireland":"Irland","Dunnyveg Castle, Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland","County Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Irland"},"nl":{"about 1370–abt 1444":"circa 1370–circa 1444","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1380–Female":"1380–Overleden","1410–1485":"1410–1485","1340–1395":"1340–1395","1345–1368":"1345–1368","about 1370":"circa 1370","before 1410":"vóór 1410","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","abt 1444":"circa 1444","1426":"1426","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1485":"1485","about 1444":"circa 1444","about 1365":"circa 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Ierland","Ireland":"Ierland","Dunnyveg Castle, Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland","County Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Ierland"},"en":{"about 1370–abt 1444":"about 1370–about 1444","1350–1426":"1350–1426","1370–1444":"1370–1444","1380–Female":"1380–Deceased","1410–1485":"1410–1485","1340–1395":"1340–1395","1345–1368":"1345–1368","about 1370":"about 1370","before 1410":"before 1410","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","abt 1444":"about 1444","1426":"1426","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1444":"1444","1410":"1410","1485":"1485","about 1444":"about 1444","about 1365":"about 1365","County Tyrone, Irland":"County Tyrone, Ireland","Ireland":"Ireland","Dunnyveg Castle, Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Dunvegan, Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","County Tyrone, Ireland":"County Tyrone, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Neill","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Kieran, Seamus, Siobhan, Dermot, Liam, Nuala, Bridie, Brigid, Conor, Fintan, John Patrick.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Néill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Niall</i>’, an Irish personal name possibly derived from <i>néal</i> ‘cloud’ (see   Neil  ).","History: Bearers of this surname mostly claim descent from Niall Noígíallach (Niall of the Nine Hostages), a legendary king of Ireland who flourished in the 5th century. His descendants, the Ui Neill dynasty, dominated Ireland, on and off, from the 6th to the 10th century. The surname itself can be traced with some confidence to one of these descendants, namely Niall Glúndubh mac Aodha (died 919), High King of Ireland from 911 to 919, with a power base in Tyrone, Ulster."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Neall","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"McNelis","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Dermot, Brendan.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Niallghuis</b> ‘son of <i>Niallghus</i>’, a personal name (intended as complimentary) composed of the personal name <i>Niall</i> (see   O'Neill  ) + <i>gus</i> ‘vigor’. In Irish the combination of [k] and [n] was generally pronounced [kr], Anglicized as the variants   McCreless   and   McCrillis  ."]},{"name":"O'Neal","meanings":["Irish (Longford, Down): variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"O'Niel","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"Odneal","meanings":["Perhaps an irregular variant of Irish   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"Nealon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Declan.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Nialláin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Niallán</i>’, a personal name formed from a diminutive of <i>Niall</i>, see   O'Neill  ,   Neil  ."]},{"name":"O'Neil","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Conn, Donal, Liam, Siobhan, Aileen, Eamon, Michael Patrick, Seamus, Sean Patrick, William Sean.","Irish (Mayo, Tipperary): variant of   O'Neill  ."]},{"name":"Neil","meanings":["Scottish, English (Lancashire), and Irish (Munster): from the Gaelic personal name <i>Niall</i> (genitive <i>Néill</i>), possibly derived from Irish <i>néal</i> ‘cloud’. In most cases the name probably represents a shortened form of the derived patronymics   McNeill   or the comparable Irish   O'Neill  .","English: variant of   Neal  ."]},{"name":"O'Neel","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Neill  ."]}]},{"name":"Conn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["name meaning ‘chief’, also used as a short form of   Connor   and of various non-Irish names beginning with the syllable <i>Con-</i> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Conn Baccach O'Neill was born about 1370, in County Tyrone, Ireland, his father, Muircheartach Ceannfhada MacÉnri, Lord of Clandeboye Ó'Néill, was 31 and his mother, Agnes Aine Cumach O'Cathain of the Isles, Limavady, was 27. He married Alice FitzGerald before 1410, in County Tyrone, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1444, in Dunvegan, Inverness-